15:
That hurt...
I mean, I'm fine! Nothing I can't
handle.
17:
Don't worry about me. Go see what's
in the treasure chest.
20: You've grown to trust me too much.
27:
I could turn on you at any time.
You'd do best to watch your back.
31:
Come on. I know you better than
that.
36:
You're the one who's always like, "If
the payoff isn't twice as great as the
risk, it's not worth my time."
38:
Even if you WERE planning to betray
me, it wouldn't be over one treasure
chest.
42:
Fine. Then why don't we go our
separate ways?
49:
No reason. Just a passing fancy.
Adieu.
60:
Everyone is a coin with two sides. On
the flip side of every smile is avarice.
And behind every veil of tears is
cunning. I've come across no
exceptions.
61:
...So why am I hoping that he'll be
different?
66:
Stop. Just stop. What promise could
there possibly be in that vacuous
smile?
71:
My, my. Seems you've caught me in
a bit of a rough spot. Not that you
ever had a snowball's chance in hell.
79:
So you had friends, did you? This
DOES pose more of a challenge...
81: I'd better withdraw and look for Alk...
85:
No, I can't rely on him... I can't rely on
anyone!
98: Haha... It seems I was right all along.
100:
Trust only leads to betrayal. Hope
only leads to heartbreak. Even Alk
was no exception.
111:
We'll be repaying our debt to you
now!
120:
Phew... You scared me... Are you hurt
at all?
124:
I'm fine, but... How'd you find this
group again?
127:
Luck. I just ran into them after we
split up.
130:
Do you remember our party
members who were heavily injured?
The two of us were Kaleidoscope
trawling, trying to earn enough
money for their hospital fees.
132:
At first, Alk left us after a few
pleasantries, but not five minutes
had passed before he came
dashing back, sweat streaming off
him.
133:
That's when he asked for help
saving his friend.
135:
When we heard that friend was you,
we couldn't sit still.
136: We owed you our lives, after all.
138:
I can't believe you did all that for
me...
141:
Please. One good turn deserves
another!
150: Well, I think you suck too.
155:
But that's just how people are.
There's no light without a shadow,
right? Everyone will have times of
strength and moments of weakness.
158:
So... do you still wanna come on this
adventure with me?
162:
Of course. For as long as you prove
useful to me.
168:
Whatever. We'd better get going. I
still have to figure out what we're
having for dinner.
174: I'm just following my heart. That's all.
